title: Tunisia attack inquest: British holidaymaker who went back
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device Tunisia attack inquest: British holidaymaker who went back 28 February 2017 Last updated at 00:58 GMT 
The inquests into the deaths of 30 Britons who died in the 2015 Tunisia beach attack end on Tuesday. 
Allen Pembroke, 62, ran back to the location of the attack after first getting his wife to safety. Related Topics
